==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin ''barbarus'' (foreigner, savage), from Greek ''barbaros'' "foreigner", onomatopoietical (mimicking foreign languages, akin to 'blah blah'.

===Pronunciation===
*(US) IPA: /bɑɹ.ˈbeɹ.i.ən/
*(UK) IPA: /bɑ.ˈbeɹ.i.ən/

===Noun===
'''barbarian'''  (''plural:'' '''[[barbarians]]''')
# An [[uncivilized]] or [[uncultured]] [[person]], often associated with fighting or other such shows of strength.

